<%- include('./partials/header') %>

<div class="container">
  <h1 class="display-4 text-center mb-2">
    API Usage
  </h1>
  <p class="text-center mb-1">All information is in JSON format.</p>
  <p class="text-center mb-3">
    The Github link for this project is
    <a href="https://github.com/darlose04/Fangraphs">here</a>.
  </p>
  <div class="mb-3 p-3 border rounded-lg border-danger">
    <h4>Notes</h4>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-3">
      <li class="list-group-item">
        All stats were downloaded from
        <a href="https://www.fangraphs.com/">Fangraphs</a> via custom made CSV
        tables.
      </li>
      <li class="list-group-item">
        Stats encompass 2002-2019.
      </li>
      <li class="list-group-item">
        Players that played for multiple teams within one season will have
        entries that detail stats for each team that player played for. So if a
        player played for two different teams, there will be two entries for
        that player, one for each team.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-3 p-3 border rounded-lg border-dark">
    <h3>Hitting Routes</h3>
    <p>
      Using GET requests, you can access the information at these routes for
      hitting:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-3">
      <li class="list-group-item">
        Get all batters stats (2002-2019):
        <code>
          /api/playerbatting
        </code>
      </li>
      <li class="list-group-item">
        Get player batting stats by season:
        <code>
          /api/playerbatting/:season
        </code>
        <p>
          <strong>Example:</strong>
          <code>
            /api/playerbatting/2010
          </code>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="list-group-item">
        Get individual batter statistics:
        <code>
          /api/playerbatting/players/:name
        </code>
        <p>
          <strong>Note: </strong>When searching for individual players, put a
          space in between the first and last name.
          <code>/api/playerbatting/players/Mike Trout</code>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="list-group-item">
        Get batters by team:
        <code>
          /api/playerbatting/teams/:team
        </code>
        <p>
          <strong>Note: </strong>This is just the team name, no city/state
          included. Same rule for spaces applies.
          <code>/api/playerbatting/teams/Red Sox</code>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="list-group-item">
        Get batters by team by year:
        <code>
          /api/playerbatting/teams/:team/:season
        </code>
        <p>
          <strong>Example:</strong>
          <code>
            /api/playerbatting/teams/White Sox/2005
          </code>
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
